I’m proud to finally announce my second #Withher talk in collaboration with @spotlightinitiative is live. This time we were honoured to have the amazing insights from @varshita.t and @seemahari as we discussed the topic on how media and Bollywood perpetuate colorism. We touched on existing films, as well as the stories and experiences of both Varshita and Seema, and how they continue to challenge these notions to make an impactful change. 

Join me as we shine a light on this important topic in an effort to end violence against women.

latestPosts.caption:
The day I dreamt of long before it was even faintly realistic. When it was still an improbable proposition. Me? On a Vogue cover? With my daughter? Naaa, that’s ludicrous. 

And now, here it is. Or actually here they are. The birth of our daughter, the birth of @indewild, the Vogue cover. 

Together we stand - 7 weeks after giving birth - showcasing the raw and unedited version of ourselves. Purely mother and daughter, eager to take on the challenges of the world, one baby step at a time. 

After two years of blood, sweat, and tears, the power of being different, has come to life. No longer will young women be trapped by societal expectations to cover their insecurities, or feel the need to falsify their persona. Introducing @indewild - a brand like no other. A movement unique to its surroundings. An independent and wild expression of freedom on the day that our “difference becomes our superpower”.

Dedicated to the young girl out there. Consumed by her innocence, mind engrossed with her aspirations to change the world. She is hopeful.
Who is she? Simple. She is a woman. She is a mother. She is you and I. ❤️
——
Huge thanks to the @vogueindia team for making this the mosttt memorable cover shoot of my life. 🙏🏽😩

latestPosts.caption:
Today, as I sign the final papers for a GLOBAL partnership between Sephora, the world’s biggest beauty retailer, and our very own @indewild, I’m honestly speechless. We’ve just launched online and in ALL @SephoraUK stores across the UK!

I vividly remember my first visit to a Sephora store 12 years ago. As a student in The Netherlands, fresh from India, I walked in with wide eyes, marveling at the luxury brands on display. I saved up €23 for my first purchase—a Dior mascara. I saw brands like Dior, Estee Lauder, Lancome, and Benefit, all so beautifully curated. But I also noticed something—none of the models looked like me.

Just 3 years into our journey, here we are. This achievement reflects both our team’s growth and Sephora’s commitment to diversity. Today, we bring our own science-backed version of 5000 years of Indian beauty wisdom to the world. We’re proudly showcasing our rich culture in a modern form.

The world is ready for India. A homegrown, ‘made in India’ brand is going to shine on Sephora shelves globally. We get to share rituals like the ‘champi’ and introduce superherbs like turmeric and ashwagandha, along with household staples like ghee. Just as India introduced Yoga and Meditation to the world, both now scientifically recognized, our beauty traditions are ready for global recognition.

I dream big and never settle for less than the best, but this moment humbles me. None of this would be possible without you. Your support, curiosity, excitement, and loving criticism built this brand brick by brick. From our dining table, while heavily pregnant and during a global pandemic, to NOW.

This one is for YOU. We started 3 years ago on a Zoom call, and today we are a community of 500,000 strong. We promise to keep evolving and bringing you the best of Ayurvedistry™. The best is yet to come!! 🚀🥹❤️
